1
00:00:01,190 --> 00:00:03,120
After we graduated high school...

2
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:07,700
I thought I'd never see you again.

3
00:00:09,940 --> 00:00:10,830
So

4
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:18,330
when we joined the same company together,
I was really happy.

5
00:00:25,770 --> 00:00:26,660
So

6
00:00:29,430 --> 00:00:31,440
I don't want to leave you anymore.

7
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:39,120
You've always been

8
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,710
someone special to me.

9
00:02:03,470 --> 00:02:07,320
[Fake Fact Lips]

10
00:02:08,539 --> 00:02:12,770
[Episode 4 Are You a Devil?]

11
00:02:12,790 --> 00:02:19,180
[Incoming Call]

12
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:25,690
Mr. Shido.

13
00:02:27,030 --> 00:02:27,650
Ugh,

14
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,570
what's with this?

15
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,000
Hm? What do you mean?

16
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:34,220
What a mess.

17
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:35,970
This is the first time
I've seen something like this.

18
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:38,670
Ah, I was just about to tidy up.

19
00:02:47,970 --> 00:02:49,220
So cold!

20
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:50,730
You've worked hard.

21
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:02,850
You've always been

22
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:07,860
someone special to me.

23
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:26,960
I'm sorry.

24
00:03:29,670 --> 00:03:30,950
I'd better go back.

25
00:03:32,070 --> 00:03:32,670
Huh?

26
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:39,140
What the heck?

27
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:41,920
Mr. Shido.

28
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,980
Mr. Shido!

29
00:03:45,890 --> 00:03:46,260
Ah?

30
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:48,550
You dropped something.

31
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:51,800
Huh? Don't be silly.

32
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:52,940
No way.

33
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,020
No, you really did.

34
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:56,900
I'm telling you I didn't!

35
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:57,740
Because...

36
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,240
Look.

37
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:00,570
Ah...

38
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,000
Are you really okay?

39
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:05,460
You were totally zoning out just now.

40
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:07,140
Well...

41
00:04:07,170 --> 00:04:08,390
It's just work stuff.

42
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:09,900
I was sorting out my thoughts.

43
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,180
Hey, this...

44
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,670
Isn't this Miss Kiritani's business card?
The one from the Secretarial Section.

45
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:14,980
How did you get this?

46
00:04:15,210 --> 00:04:16,519
That's not important.

47
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:19,839
By the way,

48
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,240
tonight we're going out for drinks

49
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:24,640
with people from the Secretarial Section.

50
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,240
Mr. Shido, are you free tonight?

51
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:29,690
One of our seniors can't make it.

52
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,100
You want me to make up the numbers?

53
00:04:32,470 --> 00:04:34,990
Sort of.

54
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:38,830
But...

55
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:41,700
Miss Kiritani might come too.

56
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:45,880
If you're trying to pursue Miss Kiritani,
please come.

57
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,450
But...

58
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:51,070
someone else is in charge of the girls.
I'm not sure who'll come.

59
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:52,870
[Kiritani Yuka]

60
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:54,670
Ah.

61
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,490
I'm sorry.

62
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:58,710
-I'd better ask someone else.
-I'll go.

63
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:01,750
What?

64
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:02,810
I'll go.

65
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:04,990
Really?

66
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,850
Thank you.

67
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,170
Nice to meet you.

68
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,560
Nice to meet you.

69
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:19,830
Okay, the last one.

70
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,660
I'm Kashimura Akari.

71
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:24,200
Although I'm in the Secretarial Section,
I'm still just serving tea and making copies.

72
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,840
I'll work hard to do more from now on.
Thank you for your support.

73
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,680
Okay.

74
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,860
Then...

75
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,230
Nice to meet you.

76
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:33,490
Nice to meet you.

77
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,630
As expected of you all.

78
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:35,620
Absolutely stunning.

79
00:05:35,620 --> 00:05:37,950
By the way, I'm really surprised
that Shido came.

80
00:05:37,950 --> 00:05:39,890
Exactly. Who invited him?

81
00:05:39,909 --> 00:05:42,040
-It's me.
-Well done.

82
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,510
I've always wanted to join you,

83
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,830
but I never got a chance.

84
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:46,840
Same goes for Kiritani from our section.

85
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,350
I told her she should attend such events
at least occasionally,

86
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:49,330
so I brought her out.

87
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:51,500
Yeah, I'm also surprised
that Miss Kiritani came.

88
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,050
You did a good job too, Ms. Matsushita.

89
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:54,400
Thank you.

90
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:55,340
Oh, it's nothing.

91
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:58,640
I figured it's not great
to just go back and forth between home and work,

92
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,840
so I mustered up the courage to come.

93
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:03,940
Then I've got to poke around tonight.

94
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:04,930
About what?

95
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,730
All kinds of things.

96
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,010
Why are you so excited?

97
00:06:10,590 --> 00:06:13,530
Sorry to keep you waiting.

98
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:15,050
Thank you.

99
00:06:15,730 --> 00:06:17,320
Well... Miss Kiritani.

100
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:18,800
I'm sorry I never reached out

101
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,200
after you gave me your business card.

102
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,980
Oh, don't worry. I know you're busy.

103
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:27,140
To be honest, I wasn't sure
if I should come tonight.

104
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,100
But I'm really glad you're here too,
Mr. Shido.

105
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:29,940
Oh, not at all.

106
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,470
Also,

107
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:37,050
I've been wanting to
have a proper talk with you, Mr. Shido.

108
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,310
Really?

109
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:39,620
Yes.

110
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,680
Mr. Shido, you look gentle,

111
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:44,370
and you're capable at work.

112
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:48,100
Honestly, those are things
women tend to love.

113
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:49,790
You really have a way with words.

114
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:51,860
How about we steal you
for the Sales Department?

115
00:06:51,860 --> 00:06:53,909
I wasn't saying that to flatter you.

116
00:06:54,370 --> 00:06:55,430
Really?

117
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,320
That makes me so happy.

118
00:06:58,470 --> 00:07:00,040
Do you really think so?

119
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:00,940
Of course.

120
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,480
Miss Kiritani, no man

121
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:04,230
would be unhappy hearing that from you.

122
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:06,370
You're such a smooth talker.

123
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,620
Well, I am a top salesperson, after all.

124
00:07:13,660 --> 00:07:14,390
Well...

125
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:17,730
Mr. Shido,
you have a really heavy workload, right?

126
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,340
No, not at all.

127
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:20,940
I'm just like everyone else.

128
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:22,620
-No.
-No.

129
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,440
How did you know that?

130
00:07:24,790 --> 00:07:27,480
Don't underestimate the Secretarial Section's
information network.

131
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:30,110
Look. The monthly reports show

132
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:32,730
that you always juggle several projects
at the same time,

133
00:07:32,730 --> 00:07:34,440
but you handle every single one well.

134
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,520
Exactly.

135
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:36,870
You're not human at all.

136
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,650
I'm totally human.

137
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:44,550
So I took the liberty
of worrying about you.

138
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:47,470
I've been wondering
if you ever relax a bit.

139
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:53,240
You've never really been good at relaxing.

140
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,390
Oh.

141
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,720
Sleeping like a baby.

142
00:08:02,450 --> 00:08:03,660
I do relax, you know.

143
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:05,510
I don't take work home with me.

144
00:08:06,050 --> 00:08:07,470
I see.

145
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:09,240
Well, that's good to hear.

146
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:12,700
Are you really that worried about me?

147
00:08:13,090 --> 00:08:14,610
Yes. I took the liberty
of worrying about you,

148
00:08:14,610 --> 00:08:16,680
and now I'm taking the liberty
of feeling relieved.

149
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:19,140
Miss Kiritani, won't you worry
about me too?

150
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:20,960
That might be a bit of a problem.

151
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,560
Don't show off your weird side now.

152
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,660
Are you already drunk?

153
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:24,340
He really has had too much.

154
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:25,260
Stop drinking.

155
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,550
-Stop drinking.
-Alright.

156
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:29,150
-I'm totally sober.
-A glass of water, please.

157
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,500
Mr. Minamide,

158
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,659
are you alright?

159
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:33,770
You've had way too much.

160
00:08:33,770 --> 00:08:35,549
I'm fine.

161
00:08:35,570 --> 00:08:37,500
-You definitely don't look fine at all.
-Huh?

162
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,559
Mr. Yotsuya? That Mr. Yotsuya, right?

163
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:42,500
Yeah, he and Mr. Shido went
to the same high school.

164
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:45,720
Neither of you are local.
What a coincidence.

165
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,050
What do you mean?

166
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,410
You two are actually quite famous.

167
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:51,590
They call you the rising stars
of Sales Section 1 and Section 2.

168
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:55,150
It's true. With this guy around,
we can barely keep up.

169
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:57,160
Are you okay?

170
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:57,770
I'm fine.

171
00:08:57,790 --> 00:08:58,440
Yes.

172
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,360
Please go back.

173
00:08:59,380 --> 00:08:59,800
No.

174
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:01,610
Please go back.

175
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:02,930
Don't say that.

176
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:05,380
I'm really nothing special.

177
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,660
Yotsuya...

178
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:10,710
is the one who's truly capable.

179
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:12,070
Huh?

180
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,160
You...

181
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,310
Mr. Shido...

182
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,700
You actually praised

183
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,330
Mr. Yotsuya?

184
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,400
Is it really that surprising?

185
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:25,340
That's the first time I've heard of it.

186
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:26,240
Same here.

187
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,160
Come on.

188
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,500
Do you two only compliment each other
when the other isn't around?

189
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:36,520
What are you talking about?

190
00:09:36,770 --> 00:09:37,930
A few days ago,

191
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:40,140
Mr. Yotsuya said the following.

192
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:45,050
Mr. Yotsuya,

193
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:46,680
you're still here?

194
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:47,870
Yes.

195
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,720
I was just about to go home
when an email came in,

196
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,450
so I've been dealing with that.

197
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:56,590
Onishi, you're hardworking too.

198
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,810
Mr. Shido works so hard,

199
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:03,190
so I just want to do something
to help him out.

200
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:05,320
You don't need to worry about that guy.

201
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,130
He overworks himself like an idiot.

202
00:10:09,570 --> 00:10:11,970
There's no need for you
to go along with him.

203
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,790
But Mr. Yotsuya,

204
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,840
you work just as hard as Mr. Shido does.

205
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:24,960
In the end, I guess I also

206
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:30,670
want to become a man
worthy of being Shido's rival.

207
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:34,960
That's what keeps me going.

208
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,840
Wow…

209
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,090
It's so touching.

210
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:46,120
So you two aren't really
at each other's throats after all.

211
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:49,550
You two really are great rivals.
That's really nice.

212
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:50,990
Yeah.

213
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:55,490
Oh, what's everyone having
for the next round?

214
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:01,920
Mr. Shido, do you have a favorite wine?

215
00:11:01,950 --> 00:11:04,070
Uh, well…

216
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:08,390
[Cabernet Sauvignon]

217
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:10,990
Cabernet Sauvignon.

218
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,300
You like this, right?

219
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:15,840
Maybe I'll pass on wine.

220
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:16,480
Really?

221
00:11:16,660 --> 00:11:18,530
Back to beer then?

222
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:20,090
Okay, beer...

223
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:25,980
Alright, I win again.

224
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:26,940
Ah!

225
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:29,800
Hey! What are you doing?

226
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:31,060
Don't touch me!

227
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:34,390
Hey, Ryo, wait.

228
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,040
Having a hard time choosing?

229
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:47,810
Have you picked your drink yet?

230
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:52,460
Ah, I'll just have the same as everyone.

231
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,810
-In the end, same as always.
-Yeah.

232
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:58,120
I'll go place the order.

233
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:00,080
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

234
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:04,430
Ah, that was really good.

235
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:06,030
I can keep going.

236
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:06,770
Oh.

237
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:08,150
What about you guys?

238
00:12:08,170 --> 00:12:10,120
I have to get up early tomorrow.

239
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,470
Really?

240
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,260
I don't have to get up early tomorrow.

241
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:14,660
Really?

242
00:12:14,690 --> 00:12:16,040
What the hell do you mean by that?

243
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,170
Well...

244
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:19,110
I was asking Miss Kiritani.

245
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:20,140
Really?

246
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:20,980
Really.

247
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:21,860
I'll go.

248
00:12:21,890 --> 00:12:22,820
-Great!
-Great!

249
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:25,950
Shido, we're heading to the next place.

250
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,610
I'm going home first.

251
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,040
-Huh?
-Huh?

252
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:31,880
Do you have to get up early tomorrow?

253
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,540
No, I just drank a bit too much.

254
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:35,520
Are you okay?

255
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:38,430
I'm fine. Thank you for asking.

256
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,300
I think I'll head back too.

257
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:43,800
Let's walk to the station together then.

258
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,480
Okay, let's go together.

259
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:46,900
Good work today.

260
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,000
Good work.

261
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:49,530
-That was great.
-Good work.

262
00:12:49,530 --> 00:12:51,360
-Alright.
-Good work.

263
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:55,830
Huh?

264
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:56,980
They left together.

265
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:01,970
-Ah.
-Let's go.

266
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,170
I had a really good time today.

267
00:13:08,170 --> 00:13:11,570
This is the first time I've ever been
to a gathering like this.

268
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:13,210
The people in our section
are pretty noisy, aren't they?

269
00:13:13,210 --> 00:13:14,120
Not at all.

270
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:16,110
Everyone's really fun.

271
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:18,400
Time just flew by.

272
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:21,820
Everyone in the Secretarial Section
is really fun too.

273
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:24,080
I got to see a different side of everyone.

274
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:28,510
People usually picture the Secretarial Section
as cold and reserved,

275
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:31,200
but we're actually just like this
in daily life.

276
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,030
Miss Kiritani, you're pretty much the same
as usual.

277
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:34,550
Yeah.

278
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,160
I'm not really good at letting loose.

279
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,600
We're actually pretty similar.

280
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:40,930
I feel the same way.

281
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,540
What about when you're with Mr. Yotsuya?

282
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:46,280
Huh?

283
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:49,660
You've known each other
since high school, right?

284
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:51,210
I was wondering if you let loose a little

285
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,870
when you're with Mr. Yotsuya.

286
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:10,860
No, not at all.

287
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,920
I've never really let loose.

288
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:15,340
With that guy, it's always just competing.

289
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:17,510
You two really are great rivals.

290
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:20,140
I kind of want one too.

291
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:23,800
Miss Kiritani.

292
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,030
What's up?

293
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:30,250
Well...

294
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:34,400
I...

295
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:40,150
Yes.

296
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:44,580
Mr. Shido.

297
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:53,760
You left this back at the restaurant.

298
00:14:54,690 --> 00:14:55,980
Thank you.

299
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,830
-You're welcome. See you tomorrow.
-Bye.

300
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:09,420
Mr. Shido.

301
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:15,460
I'll...

302
00:15:16,570 --> 00:15:17,440
take the bus.

303
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,000
Ah.

304
00:15:20,870 --> 00:15:22,860
I'll take the train.

305
00:15:29,710 --> 00:15:30,170
Well...

306
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:31,320
Bye.

307
00:15:33,610 --> 00:15:34,060
Okay.

308
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:36,230
Bye.

309
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,300
[Yotsuya Ryo]

310
00:15:56,330 --> 00:16:02,840
[Block this number]

311
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:08,740
Zen.

312
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:10,410
Can you hear me?

313
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:14,730
[Yotsuya Ryo]

314
00:16:12,330 --> 00:16:13,270
Zen.

315
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:15,650
Oh no!

316
00:16:19,060 --> 00:16:19,820
Well...

317
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:21,470
What's wrong?

318
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:23,770
Nothing.

319
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:26,330
I was just at a place called Break,

320
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:29,140
drinking with the girls
from the Secretarial Section.

321
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:31,600
Mm, I know that place.

322
00:16:31,940 --> 00:16:33,340
Pretty good food, right?

323
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:34,720
Yeah.

324
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,660
Was Miss Kiritani there too?

325
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:39,710
Yeah.

326
00:16:41,380 --> 00:16:44,720
Really? So, why are you calling?

327
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:46,150
Huh?

328
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:49,220
Well...

329
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,510
The girls from the Secretarial Section

330
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,640
seemed to want to have dinner with you.

331
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:56,830
Huh? That's it?

332
00:16:57,810 --> 00:16:59,560
Yes.

333
00:17:00,330 --> 00:17:01,120
Not going.

334
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:02,670
Not interested.

335
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:09,720
Say something.

336
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:10,270
Huh?

337
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:13,329
Ah, no...

338
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:15,650
Ah, T-shirt.

339
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:17,109
T-shirt?

340
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,300
The one I borrowed before.

341
00:17:19,470 --> 00:17:20,349
Oh.

342
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,150
I want to return it to you.

343
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,480
Come over now.

344
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,839
Huh? Why?

345
00:17:27,170 --> 00:17:28,430
No particular reason.

346
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,530
Because it's a hassle
to take it back again.

347
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:31,660
None of my business!

348
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:32,750
Whatever.

349
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:34,830
Ah, wait...

350
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:42,010
What am I doing?

351
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,360
Zen!

352
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:44,920
Ryo?

353
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:50,590
The T-shirt.

354
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,180
You didn't bring it with you, did you?

355
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,460
You're not the type
to call people normally.

356
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:00,920
Ah...

357
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:03,440
You're drunk, aren't you?

358
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:06,730
Did you

359
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,850
want to see me?

360
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:09,670
No way.

361
00:19:10,340 --> 00:19:11,740
I thought I had it with me.

362
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,430
Forget it.

363
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:15,700
We can sort the shirt out anytime.

364
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,130
Since this hardly ever happens,

365
00:19:19,130 --> 00:19:20,790
I'll help you sober up.

366
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,300
Let's go for a walk.

367
00:19:23,580 --> 00:19:25,440
Since I didn't bring the T-shirt,

368
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:26,590
you could just head back home.

369
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:28,190
Are you a devil?

370
00:19:29,260 --> 00:19:31,120
You're the one who told me to come.

371
00:19:33,270 --> 00:19:34,360
I'm not going back.

372
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:39,220
Because I want to spend a little more time
with you, even if it's just a little more.

373
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:39,830
Let's go.

374
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:42,790
Really?

375
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:29,780
Hey.

376
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:33,320
Have you ever been inside that building?

377
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,280
No.

378
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:35,670
There seem to be

379
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:38,030
a lot of interesting shops inside.

380
00:21:39,810 --> 00:21:41,600
How about we go check it out sometime?

381
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,140
As a date.

382
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:43,760
Date?

383
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:44,800
That's lame.

384
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:47,630
You're always like this.

385
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:49,760
You forget all about our rivalry
right away.

386
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,000
I don't have time
to go on a date with you.

387
00:21:55,290 --> 00:21:56,950
There seems to be a restaurant

388
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:59,710
that serves
your favorite braised pork rice.

389
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:00,720
Huh?

390
00:22:01,810 --> 00:22:03,850
I've never told anyone
I like braised pork rice.

391
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:04,850
Before,

392
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,900
when I took you out,

393
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,580
you were eating it so happily.

394
00:22:10,150 --> 00:22:11,480
You even remember that?

395
00:22:13,230 --> 00:22:14,810
You're really observant.

396
00:22:14,990 --> 00:22:15,650
Hmph.

397
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:18,620
I've always been keeping a close eye
on you.

398
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:19,880
You're unbelievable.

399
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:22,860
Well,

400
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:26,250
next time I win, you can treat me.

401
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:27,060
Huh?

402
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:29,530
You mean our work rivalry?

403
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:31,280
Of course.

404
00:22:31,910 --> 00:22:33,250
As a reward for winning,

405
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,740
one bowl of braised pork rice
isn't nearly enough.

406
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:36,830
Why? Isn't it delicious?

407
00:22:37,130 --> 00:22:38,530
Yeah, it is.

408
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:43,100
Yeah, you're right.

409
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:49,350
Hey.

410
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:51,570
-Zen.
-Yeah.

411
00:22:54,890 --> 00:22:57,080
Once our rivalry is settled,

412
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:00,810
what...

413
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:03,580
will become of us?

414
00:23:07,510 --> 00:23:08,110
Who knows?

415
00:23:12,260 --> 00:23:13,590
Do you think we might not

416
00:23:14,180 --> 00:23:15,780
even be able to stay friends?

417
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:30,110
Hey.

418
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:31,720
Zen.

419
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:33,540
What?

420
00:23:37,510 --> 00:23:39,310
Maybe we should just call off...

421
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:41,380
this kind of rivalry.

422
00:24:59,490 --> 00:25:02,800
[In the Next Episode]

423
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:02,310
Mr. Shido.

424
00:25:02,390 --> 00:25:03,420
Sorry.

425
00:25:02,830 --> 00:25:05,950
[Episode 5 I Just Don't Get It]

426
00:25:03,450 --> 00:25:04,300
Oh.

427
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:06,510
Mr. Shido.

428
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:09,100
From the perspective of a bystander,
Mr. Shido, you're too busy.

429
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:10,750
Wow, a great subordinate
is really shining.

430
00:25:10,750 --> 00:25:12,980
So dishonest.
